   "source": [
    "# Cell Neighborhoods Mapping and Functional Characterization\n",
    "High-resolution spatial transcriptomic data provides invaluable insights into cellular organization and interactions within their neighborhoods. These spatially organized neighborhoods play crucial roles in tissue functions and disease progression. This tutorial offers detailed instructions on how to perform cell neighborhood analysis using the package. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "9fe886ae",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import scanpy as sc\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib\n",
    "from matplotlib.pyplot import rc_context\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.colors as mcolors\n",
    "cmap = mcolors.LinearSegmentedColormap.from_list('WhRd',[\"#e5e5e5\", \"#fffacd\", \"red\", \"darkred\"], N=256)  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "837cde03-95a2-47a3-9e2b-add9b37b5793",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pySTIM as pst"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "2314daa3-2783-49b7-bc3e-808853e1486e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "adata_vis = pst.load_Visium_data()\n",
    "adata_xe = pst.load_Xenium_data()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "41e756ee-2101-4c85-bfa9-ce673263a8b4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Identify Cell Neighborhoods\n",
    "\n",
    "We offers two methods to define cell neighborhoods: __fixed radius__ or __fixed K-nearest neighbors (KNN)__. To specify the method, set the `mode` parameter to either '__radius__' or '__knn__'. You also need to specify the expected number of neighborhoods, which can be manually tuned by checking the cell type enrichment in neighborhoods. The calculated cell neighborhood results will be saved to `adata.obs[\"CN\"]`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c145f739-fc7a-418d-9158-e7e4825a2aa4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Using Radius-Based Method"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "9032b565-135a-4dec-af87-e1dafff1b68c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pst.calculate_cn(adata_xe, mode='radius', radius=10,\n",
    "                group = \"ident\", cluster = \"celltype\",\n",
    "                n_neighborhoods=10, figsize=(8,4))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a2d17f25-a005-4749-b478-9233013316b8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Using KNN-based Method"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "6df6165e-47ea-4621-84dd-e3956c4b9cf2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pst.calculate_cn(adata_xe, mode='knn', k=10, \n",
    "                group = \"ident\", cluster = \"celltype\",\n",
    "                n_neighborhoods=10, figsize=(8,4))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3b6e41ed-925e-4002-9f8d-bcf8b83b5b20",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Visualize the cell neighborhood organization in spatial. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "16fdec9e-e99d-4d8d-99d3-062523c6509d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/html": [
       "<div style=\"vertical-align: middle;\"><strong>Set3</strong> </div><div class=\"cmap\"><img alt=\"Set3 colormap\" title=\"Set3\" style=\"border: 1px solid #555;\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></div><div style=\"vertical-align: middle; max-width: 514px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between;\"><div style=\"float: left;\"><div title=\"#8dd3c7ff\" style=\"display: inline-block; width: 1em; height: 1em; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; border: 1px solid #555; background-color: #8dd3c7ff;\"></div> under</div><div style=\"margin: 0 auto; display: inline-block;\">bad <div title=\"#00000000\" style=\"display: inline-block; width: 1em; height: 1em; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; border: 1px solid #555; background-color: #00000000;\"></div></div><div style=\"float: right;\">over <div title=\"#ffed6fff\" style=\"display: inline-block; width: 1em; height: 1em; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; border: 1px solid #555; background-color: #ffed6fff;\"></div></div>"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.colors.ListedColormap at 0x7f3acd00d310>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 12,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.get_cmap(\"Set3\", lut = 10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "e36a7987-3037-4f77-bba9-a79440a0a763",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cmap_CN = plt.get_cmap(\"Set3\", lut = 10)\n",
    "hex_colors = [plt.cm.colors.rgb2hex(cmap_CN(i)) for i in range(cmap_CN.N)]\n",
    "adata_xe.uns['CN_colors'] = hex_colors"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "919df024-0bfd-47ca-be49-3d42953d6838",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pst.plot_scatter(adata_xe, color_by=\"CN\", ptsize=1, seed=123, dpi=80, alpha=1, legend_col=1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b660ae14-a84c-4219-a230-150958bc6996",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Proximity Enrichment Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Proximity enrichment analysis evaluates the enrichment frequency between cell type pairs using permutation-based tests. The significance of spatial relationships is determined by comparing observed frequencies to those from randomly permuted datasets. The output result is the enrichment z-scores. Note that this step may take a considerable amount of time (~10 minutes for 1000 permutations) when the cell number is large."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "0a2c109c-886d-4263-b63b-da795ad6cda2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Total number of 85880 cells\n",
      "Calculating observed interactions...\n",
      "Permutation iterations: 0...\n",
      "Permutation iterations: 100...\n",
      "Permutation iterations: 200...\n",
      "Permutation iterations: 300...\n",
      "Permutation iterations: 400...\n",
      "Permutation iterations: 500...\n",
      "Permutation iterations: 600...\n",
      "Permutation iterations: 700...\n",
      "Permutation iterations: 800...\n",
      "Permutation iterations: 900...\n",
      "Finished!\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "df = pst.calculate_enrichment(adata_xe, groupby = \"celltype\", n_permutations = 1000, \n",
    "                              niche_radius = 15, spatial_key = \"spatial\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5175a5ac-bfce-4086-92cf-9b48704f166a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Visualize the enrichment as heatmaps."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 134,
   "id": "a06c6b20-6dbe-4687-bbc8-6de0703c2293",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x500 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pst.plot_connectivity(df, cmap = \"Reds\", dpi = 100, figsize = (6,5))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "aaf23478-8737-4c79-a185-e79a1b89f893",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Visualize the results as a graph network. In this network, each node represents a cell type, the node size indicates the cell type frequency, and edges connecting two cell types represent the enrichment scores. To enhance clarity, specify the cell types you want to highlight."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 133,
   "id": "925e0363-0d84-450f-8b53-304cca30b450",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "color_dict = dict(zip(adata_xe.obs.celltype.cat.categories, adata_xe.uns[\"celltype_colors\"]))\n",
    "\n",
    "pst.plot_network(adata_xe, df, color_map = color_dict, groupby = \"celltype\",  \n",
    "                 highlight = [\"PTS2\",\"PTS3\",\"Pod\",\"Glom-EC\",\"ICA\",\"ICB\",\"PC\",\"CNT\"], seed = 3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b785e33f-bb6d-4da1-803f-a514150c92af",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Functional Analysis of Neighborhoods\n",
    "\n",
    "Next, we need to transfer the calculated CN labels to the Visium dataset for further analysis. Visium data provides whole transcriptome information, allowing for comprehensive functional analysis of the neighborhoods identified within the Xenium dataset. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "62ad3f1b-0844-49de-afd4-8f04518c48a1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "adata_vis = pst.add_metadata(adata_vis, adata_xe, anchor_dict, col = \"CN\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "682742c9-799c-4c9f-a66a-9b91d2539aff",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Once the CN labels are transferred, compute the differential expression within the identified neighborhoods. This provide a more detailed molecular characterization compared to limited gene panel in Xenium dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "2d943deb-587d-40b4-9f35-51d607fb7e1f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sc.tl.rank_genes_groups(adata_vis, groupby = 'CN', method='wilcoxon', use_raw=False)\n",
    "de_df = sc.get.rank_genes_groups_df(adata_vis, group = None)\n",
    "marker_genes = de_df.groupby('group').head(3)['names'].unique().tolist()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "id": "b6bc6ef6-cce9-4d64-a852-b445db4b79ce",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "adata_vis.layers[\"scaled\"] = sc.pp.scale(adata_vis, copy=True).X"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "id": "f7ac32f9-6be1-43c2-8d24-c8dd40994bf5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 3225x1350 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "with rc_context({'figure.figsize': (8, 3), 'figure.dpi': 300}):\n",
    "    sc.pl.matrixplot(adata_vis, marker_genes, 'CN', dendrogram=False, layer='scaled', \n",
    "                               vmin=-2, vmax=2, cmap='RdBu_r')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5b8b426b-4c8d-41e9-8362-30a4defd4612",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Additionally, perform gene set enrichment analysis to identify molecular signatures within specific neighborhoods. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "id": "3fd33f99-a124-4494-927d-56a7e0360c42",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "CN3_de = sc.get.rank_genes_groups_df(adata_vis, group = \"3\", pval_cutoff = 0.05, log2fc_min = 1).names.to_list()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 69,
   "id": "e8243129-8ad2-4b92-95d0-b0f19f72d2a3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "enrichr_library = 'GO_Biological_Process_2023'"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 103,
   "id": "46239daa-f531-4983-8c4f-b7b3578b5d3e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x450 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pst.gesa(CN3_de, enrichr_library, show_number = 10, bar_color = '#80b1d3')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 104,
   "id": "9b1857b3-f811-435a-a0ec-a7f8f3ae7e64",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x450 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "enrichr_library = 'MSigDB_Hallmark_2020'\n",
    "pst.gesa(CN3_de, enrichr_library, show_number = 10, bar_color = '#80b1d3')"
   ]
  }
